  Kernel::Orientation_2  


A model for this must provide:
 

    
          Orientation   

         
          
             
    fo.operator() (     
      Kernel::Point_2  p,  Kernel::Point_2  q,  Kernel::Point_2  r)     
                
    returns   LEFT_TURN  , if  r  lies to the left of the oriented 
line  l  defined by  p  and  q , returns   RIGHT_TURN   if  r  
lies to the right of  l , and returns   COLLINEAR   if  r  lies
on  l .
            

  Refines  AdaptableFunctor  (with three arguments)
 

  See Also   CGAL::orientation    

    Next:    Kernel::Orientation_3   


    
 
